  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<p style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Things to see and do</strong></p>
<p>With a large ferry port and train station, you won’t run out of things to do in Desenzano. This is one the best places to stay on Lake Garda if you’ve got sightseeing on your agenda. You can travel all round the lake by ferry - head for a leisurely day to<span> </span>Sirmione to try their famous gelato. Or jump on a train for some city sightseeing. There’s so much to see and do in <a data-udi="umb://document/41229767036d47f28a27ac846e23458b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/41229767036d47f28a27ac846e23458b}" title="Verona">Verona</a> or <a data-udi="umb://document/201893063f65496384a9bd17846543a7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/201893063f65496384a9bd17846543a7}" title="Venice">Venice</a>. Don’t forget about the smaller cities though, they can be a real hidden gem.</p>
<p>There's lots to see and do in the town itself, too:</p>
<ul>
<li>Desenzano’s castle looks out over the town and you get some great views over the lake from the tower entrance. You can walk around the walls here and take in the history.</li>
<li>The archaeological museum is a must-see if you’re interested in history. They’ve got a great selection of Bronze-Age artefacts. Grab a combination ticket that includes the castle to save a few euros.</li>
<li>Head to the town’s Roman villa to get an idea of how wealthy Romans used to live when they holidayed on the lakes. It was built more than 2,000 years ago and you can wander around the ruins and see the mosaics left behind. We recommend watching the short video that explains the original layout of the house.</li>
<li>See the Last Supper by Tiepolo at the Cathedral of Santa Maria Maddalena – a 16th Century church. You can’t miss it – it’s in the centre of Desenzano and it’s a great option to escape the crowds for a while.</li>
<li>The Parco Sigurta botanical gardens are just south of Desenzano but we love visiting them while we’re here. It’s a great, wide-open space where you can get back to nature.</li>
</ul>]]></thingsToDo>
